comments: Everything worked well! I enjoyed reading and reflecting on each scenario. I felt the instructions and scenarios were clear. Thank you!
I have no comments or suggestions.
The study was enjoyable and an engaging exercise.
I think it would be a smart idea to have a definition of hierarchial at the beginning of the study.

The question worded "make sure X's benefits are as high as their own" seemed a bit vague, and I wavered a bit for the first few questions on how I actually should interpret it. I ended up deciding I should read it as "as high or higher" rather than "equal to their own," but it would have been very helpful to have that clear in the question's wording.
Elaborate on what a hierarchal relationship exactly means?
